caption: Good and affordable Thai food very close to campus. I had so many meals there when I was in school. I would recommend it in a heart beat.
Their beef in oyster sauce is really great.
The customer service is always rapid, awesome atmosphere, super nice employees. Will visit again when I am in town.

This is my go to Thai restaurant around this area. I always do takeout. The interior is nothing fancy, but the food is really good. It differs from time to time based on which family member is cooking, but the variance is a good thing. The portions are big and the prices reasonable.

Best Thai place  in the area! Excellent food that’s always high quality and just as you expect it, and they take really good care of vegetarian/allergic customers. Most anything can be made vegetarian and they even called me back to confirm allergens, ask if I eat egg and such. Sweet family owned place you can make your regular spot. Good portion sizes, no hidden up-charges, and I can always eat one dish for two meals. (Also, they are always wearing masks and being really COVID safe, nice patio to eat at outside in the summer)
Good service, crazy noodles and curries are good.
Use to eat here when we lived in the area in 2003. Came back for take out and was as remembered. Very friendly and food was super tasty as it was then.
Very good food and the place is nice, we can wait you to open
Used to be one of my favourite take out places.
Great thai food enough said
Great food and service during these times.
Lotta money for bland microwaved food. Barely warm a min after I got it.

Thai bowl's is by far the BEST Thai place I have been to. No other places compare to their wide noodle pad see ew or chicken pad thai and the amazing flavor! Such a nice family business too. Definitely a go-to even Kanye West has been seen eating here by fellow UIC students since campus is close by.
Best Thai in the city
Solid Thai
A top scene for tasty Thai food. I give this place two thumbs up. Really nothing but great experiences here, so I will be back. Prices are reasonable I would say.
Delicious! Thank you for accommodating my food allergies 💜
I love thai bowl! Been eating here for over 15 years and they've never disappointed. The patio area can use a face lift though, it's infested with bugs
Good food

The food is mediocre at best. I understand that quarantine has affected many businesses, but this place has raised their prices and lowered their quality significantly. The menu is hard to read and the food does not reflect the description on the menu. For example, I ordered the Thai iced tea which was 70% ice and 30% drink. And my gf ordered the pork wonton bowl; the pork was dry and old tasting and covered carelessly with pepper. The cashier lady was rude and very slow with her service. I would not recommend this place to anyone, and I will not be returning to eat here for as long as I walk on the earth.
Tried this spot in the past with a friend and I am hooked since then. I liked the awesome atmosphere and delicious food and beverages. 5 stars.
They are closed until further notice
This spot never fails to impress. They serve fresh dishes for convenient pricing, there are no long waits even when the place is full.
Thai food

We came to this spot for lunch. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was very successful. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The meal was fresh and delicious. We had a great time and we shall absolutely come back again. Highly recommended.
Quaint little place with good food and good pricing. Ambiance could've been better. Good for dine and dash for students

I celebrated my nomination earlier this evening in this excellent restaurant. happy to tell that we had a pleasant evening and the place was evidently one of the reasons for the outstanding evening. The crew  participated in a pleasant way, the food was tasty and my friends were so  pleased. We shall no dout return for more joyful events. thanks very much.
Amazing home like food
Favorite Thai food.
Best thai green curry in the city. Amazing
Good spot and good food!
I have been coming here for years, absolutely delicious.
The food was great - watch out! So wondrously hot food ! large amts, tasty & all a family afair!
I've eaten and enjoyed Thai Bowl's food for years—can't picture Taylor Street without it. Friendly service and respectable value.
terrible service. food is fine.
Good thai food
The food here is disgusting. I have given this place 2 tries. This place is nowhere near decent thao cuisine.
Meal took time to arrive but when it came it was worth it.
Classic.
the chicken pad thai is great. never a bad experience.

It has been twice that I have ordered ahead of time and every time I get there the food is not ready l. The third time this happened I was furious because I seen the lady shot out the order when I paid. I immediately was angry at the fact that im going to have to wait 20 minutes like i had done in the past for food I ordered 30 minutes ago! She said it takes a long time and I looked at the restaurant and it was empty. So disappointing because the crazy noodles are my favorite there!
I been coming here for years, the food is great and the prices are as well, plus is byob!

The food is fine (7/10). I dined in alone and was surprised when the cashier lady forced me to put tip on the bill. I mean tip should be optional and can be either cash/card. It's not her business and she was a little rude honestly.

Used to come here often. Arrived at 12:13pm and placed a togo order with only 2 other patrons in the place that had their food and were eating. Still waiting on the food at 1:11pm. Our order was 2 noodle entrees and an order of crab rangoons. Asked the front staff and they said 'its coming'. Well, we won't be coming back. Someone please sell them a POS system.
Decent food however they don't have brown rice anymore.
Food was good
Good food and good service.

This is a small Thai spot with really good noodles and fries rice! The beef curry noodles were outta this world..the flavors were so unique and amazing..jus a flavor bomb! We ordered fish cakes,t beef curry noodles and the Thai bowl mixed fried rice. The fried rice was ok,nothing great and so we're the fish cakes. But u jus have to order the beef curry noodles or the same version in fried rice. Never tried this kinda flavor before..so tripping over it!

Crazy Noodles happens to be my first choice. The spicy red sauce has a sweet and fiery kick. Crab Rangoons pair well with just about anything for an appetizer. They are piping hot and fresh, during the week at lunch time, mm mmm. Take your friends here for a bite to eat. You shall enjoy a delicious Thai meal here.
Best pad Thai with chicken in the city
Nope nope and nope. Got the Pad Se Eww and egg roll. Both were stale and inedible. Disappointing experience. I do not recommend
Excellent Pad Thai! Great Service!
Really great food. Tastes like a family-cooked meal. Try the Pad Thai, the chicken fried rice, and the Thai Iced Tea 👍🏼
Food is cheap and good. Interior could be cleaner
Great food, but the place isn't very nice, and not well-managed.
(Translated by Google) Excellent place, delicious food and good treatment! Highly recommended  (Original) Excelente lugar, riquísima la comida y buen trato! Muy recomendable.
I enjoy Asian food.
Nice place to eat.

An old favorite among my gaming cronies at UIC, this is one of your best choices for Thai cuisine on the near west side. Yes, the furniture might be plastic chairs and older wood tables. But did you come here to eat, or did you come here to ogle the furniture?
Very decent prices! Food is amazing and well cooked.
Fast and delicious!
Great food and great service at a reasonable price.
Good place to sit and eat would friends. The prices are relatively cheap for the amount of food you get. I recommend the duck Pad Thai.
Amazing Thai!!
Great food, at a good price.
Food is really good Israel great service that was wonderful I recommend anybody to visit
Very nice place. Food was good and it didn't take long for them to prepare the meal.  My visit was during lunch hour.  Staff were great!

I love how Thai Bowl highlights the textural and flavor elements in Thai cuisine, all with the local spin of IL produce. I also like that for a Michelin star, more high profile restaurant, they don't shy away from heat and spice! Still remains one of my fav favs in all of Chicago.
They have a weird way of calculating tip.
Delicious food and  afordable
Best chicken pad thai I ever had, as well as many other dishes  and enormously generous amount. Employees are soo kind. I drive over a hour just to get their food.
Food was alright and service was fantastic. I can't get over how old and how much updating it needs though. It could be such a beautiful place! But didn't seem very clean
AWFUL
Love the PadThai. I have Tofu or no keat and add brocolli and pineapples.
Great variety of noodle dishes and all wonderfully spiced and delicious. It's really affordable too.
Awesome place/great food really like the Thai ice tea... Parking can be a pain to find depending on time of day/evening. no fault of restaurants though...
Plentiful portions, great prices, vegan options as well. The staff asked if we were vegan or vegi and understood the difference when recommending items
Nothing has changed since my days in college.  Still just as great. 😁

I love this place, its affordable, quick, tasty, and refreshing. Their pad thai with duck is legit (I've been to Thailand, its exactly like a good home-cooked meal from a friendly village in the outskirts of a friendly village). I do wish lime, more crushed peanuts, and more bean sprouts accompanied the pad thai though.

Pad Woonsen is the only dish I've tried there but I can vouch for it...it's really good! If you're not into spicy food, that's your dish right there. A hot sauce is provided for people who prefer living on the edge. My Muslim bros, sadly Pad Woonsen is the only dish you can have over there
Delicious rice and great service, pretty nice setting.

I used to love this place but now I don't . The food is not consistent, they need to get their recipes together. I need consistently delicious Thai food. Oh but they do have the best egg rolls, always!!!

Cheap but good quality food. Small but clean. Friendly staff and little wait time. Although it doesn’t have many choices in main course, I will recommend to try chicken or combo fried rice items over there, they are really delicious. Among starter, spring roll is the best.
Expensive but decent pad Thai. As far as Asian places downtown go, I would eat somewhere else.
I love this place, but I currently can't order here because they say the number is disconnected. Anyone have an updated phone number?
Great food...e.g....Basil chicken; Beef in Oyster Sauce; Bami Won ton Soup

I have been a customer for 18 years..this food is absolutely delicious!! The Asian ladies taking my orders are very respectful and sweet!! I would totally recommend this place if you want a food coma! P.s you should totally try the shrimp Pat tie , and the chicken fried rice..also the spring rolls are a must have!
Great food selection, I've had a couple soups from here that I've loved, but their Thai Iced Coffee tastes oddly bitter and too sweet at the same time-- stay away from that!
Unnecessarily oily food. The egg rolls are completely avoidable and the rice dishes weren’t cooked properly so you can taste the uncooked spices. The Thai ice tea was probably the only thing on point

Shrimp pad thai was super sweet.While putting my order in the Asian lady keep asking me is my order to go like she didnt want me to dine in ..Place is dated,Asian lady was racist and pad thai was extremely sweet..
Used to be cheap. Not so anymore. Food is good.

We pass by this so many times and I'm so upset we haven't eaten here before! It's so delicious!! Even though they were closong soon, everything we ordered was made fresh! The peanut sauce for the chicken satay was incredible! We can't wait to try other dishes, we some how managed to eat most of our bowl and hit a pleasant food coma.
Authentic thai taste. Just loved it 👌👌

Amazing Thai food at a great price.  I have been going here since my freshman year in college (2003).  My go to dish is the Jade noodles; I have been unable to find a Thai dish with this unique flavor in any of the many other Thai restaurants I have been to.  The only issue I have is that the price has recently gone up on most of their dishes, though it is still relatively cheap for a city restaurant.
Best Thai in Chicago.  I have been a customer for 12 years.  Blessings.
Great place for thai very friendly and helpful
The food and service was very good. Waitress actually thanked us for coming
Decent priced, a bit stuffy inside and greasy food but very satisfied.
It was a good Thai food (not excellent) with reasonable prices.

i love their chicken pad thai and their quick and friendly service. they’re quiet and super fast in the kitchen. they also treat all customers respectfully, even the ones that come in throwing hissy fits. thankful that these ladies are still in business, i highly recommend this cute spot!!
Last time I did not find the food very tasty but this time I ordered the red and green curry. Both of them were amazing. I would suggest going for the thai red or green curry.
My favorite Thai place in Chicago!
Really good Thai food. Soup is exquisite. Entree options are plenty.
Decent priced, a bit stuffy inside and greasy food but very satisfied. Shrimp shumai is a waste: it's blended,frozen, and bland. Hard pass- Ordered the crazy noodles.
Mmmmm
Not great. I used to come here a lot in the past. Seems like the food and service used to be better.
Good
AWESOME food my fav is the hot and souer soup
Great pad Thai and basil chicken bowls!
Good comfort food, for the price
I moved to GA and I SO miss this place. I visit every time I'm home. My favorite is the Thai Bowl Mixed. It's fried rice accompanied curry, beef, chicken, shrimp and crab meat, It's SO good!!!
They were not very pleasant
Great Soup and pad thai,,

Really good hole in the wall place to grub where you get a lot of bang for your buck. The bowls are all fairly priced at about $8-$10 and are filling. They can easily be shared between 2 people and be enough. The Thai Bowl Mixed is the thing to get. Fried rice with everything; chicken, beef, crab, and shrimp. Insanely delicious. The only thing keeping me from giving it 5 stars is that it looks a little dirty on the inside. You know authentic hole in the wall places are delicious, but you'd never want to see their kitchen.
One of the best Thai places on Taylor
Awesome place. Good prices great food
Food is okay. But it’s quick and convenient.
Cold in there, soup was nasty!! No flavor at all!!! Needs remodeling

Ordered here Pad Thai and pin duck noodles. The pad thai was good. But the pin duck noodles was mediocre because there was lack of duck meat in my dish. There was only 10-15% duck meat in my dish, the rest was noodles.
Great pad thai!

When I was a student at UIC (15 years ago) this was the spot for some great Thai Food. Delicious food and people there are so courteous. Every time I'm in there area, I just have to get the Rama Chicken. They haven't changed. It's great home-cooking.
Great food, simple service ! Prices just went up —but still considerably worth it for the big servings!
Didn't like the food or the place.

Holy schnikes.  This little hole in the wall Thai place is not for you if you want ambience. But...,   if you want some great tasting Thai food at a reasonable price then you need to visit here.  One of the best Hot and Sour soups in the city.  And the food is delicious. And you get to pick from three almost empty soap dispensers in the bathroom that tilts slightly towards the North.  Very reasonable prices and great tastes. Give it a try.

I'm very glad my beautiful and intelligent date overshadowed my overall dining experience. Very simple cozy atmosphere set the theme for good home cooked Thai food, I left very unimpressed with taste of food. Vegetarian friendly, Pad Thai was very ketchupy otherwise it was okay, most credit goes to the hot sauce. Green Curry was not the slightest bit spicy otherwise it was okay, most credit goes to the hot sauce. My friend says she enjoyed the food, I don't believe she was being honest. Still, if she wanted to stop in again, I would and she would be the only reason.
The food is awesome. Service friendly.
Delicious food 😍 Kind staff 🤗
Great food
Great food!
Good food but could be cleaned and more updated..also the wait with no one in the place is a bit much.
Strong flavor and good portion!
Fire🔥
Amazing food, highly recommend their Thai Bowl freeze ( you can choose two flavors, my favorite is mango and lychee)
Love the food

I HAVE DEVELOPED OVER THE YEARS A LOVE OF THAI FOOD. IT CAME FROM ONE PLACE AND ONE PLACE ONLY NEAR MY WORK AND I WENT AS OFTEN AS I COULD. SIMPLE, PLEASANT, DELICIOUS,  HREAT PRICE.  ONE OF THE ONLY PLACES THAT SERVES THEIR DISHES WITH A WARM PEANUT SAUCE.  I ALWAYS LOOK FOR IT ELSEWHERE.  YOU GOTTA COME HERE TO SEE
The ginger chicken rice bowl is great. Needs some interior and exterior work tho

I ordered the beef Pad Thai, not expecting much. It had no spice but at least they put the giant red bottle of chili so I could add my own. No crushed peanuts, but there was a slice of lime which was nice. The beef was tough, but at least it was totally lean meat (no fat or sinew). Noodles were not overcooked which was nice. There were some green onions, not much. But I was just happy to get lunch after running through a thunderstorm.
I had the best chicken fried rice. It was a little spicy though.
Nice outdoor seating
A little overpriced but good is good
Delicious
Delicious food and wonderful patio.
Best hole in the wall for Thai! Everything so far is so good and I'm trying everything on the menu day by day. Sweet, salty,spicy, sour, and fishy is all there!
Very reasonable prices coupled with delicious food and friendly service.  Eat outside on the patio during warm weather.  Can't miss with beef lard nar, chicken satay, rama chicken or cucumber salad.
Good food, good service, clean place
Get the THAI BOWL MIXED FRIED RICE. It's the bomb!
My favorite Thai place on taylor st!
Great

Nice place for basic Thai food at a good price.  Small
Very near to our residence, clean and good customer service
One of the best Thai restaurant in the area.
Love their Pad Thai and soups!
Food is great! Customer service and having to ask for silverware napkins andcwaterv... terrible!!!

Solid food and not too expensive. Nice small dining area. They have a TV going inside. The outside seating area in warmer moths looks very nice.
OK. Cheap, decent Thai food.
Yum yum yum! Fresh creations of authentic Thai food. They have a nice space in the courtyard during  warmer weather for al fresco dining.
Love it
I went here alot when i attended UIC, now if im in the area ill seek out a nice big bowl of pad thai and enjoy the food with happiness
One of favorite places near UIC for some Thai food. Quite authentic I heard
This is a go-to for good thai noodles.
Chicken fried rice or pad Thai. Cannot go wrong.
Pin noodles duck...so good.
Good food. Good price.
I'm from Dallas, Tx and this is the best place to eat In Chicago, good food for a low price and beautiful scenery to eat outside!
Awesome food - especially get the Jade Noodles meal, wow delicious!  Can't wait to go back!

If you're a student of UIC (west and east campuses) and would like decent and cheap Thai food, then this place is good for you. And when I say cheap, don't expect much.  They have outside sitting when the day is nice. The service staff is quick about serving you. The place is not the fanciest I've seen but anywhere in Little Italy it's hard to find that. I find that the TV that's always tuned on CNN to be annoying, but they have a TV that's tuned in to the latest current events.
Delicious with great atmosphere
The food wasn't that good.
Not the fanciest place, but the food is always great. I highly recommend the Pad Thai. It's the only thing I ever order here!
Tasty lunch for a decent price. You get your food pretty fast after ordering, so its a perfect place for lunch break.
Always enjoy Thai Bowl.  Nice quiet space to have great conversation and enjoy good food!
The Rama chicken was great.
Probably the cheapest Thai food around UIC, and the portions are OK.

Worst service ever after 1 hour of waiting rung up to be told it was on its way. Waiter 30 mines rung back up to be told it was on its way and will be with us shortly.... after 2 hours of waiting I rung up to complain and was told it was just going out the door with it.. I asked to talk to the manager but was told he was cooking and could not talk.. I canceled would not recommend at all !!!!!!!!!!
Been here many times. Walking distance from UIC. Try the Chicken Curry Fried Rice.
Good food and service.
My 2 personal favorite dishes are the Bamee wonton noodles and the panang curry beef. Also the Thai iced coffee is really good

I've always found that the smaller places, that aren't much to look at, serve the best food. No, the decor isn't great, but I'm not there to eat the decor. I go to Thai Bowl for delicious food and it is genuinely one of my favorite Thai restaurants.

Worst service I have ever experienced! I have offered take out from Thai bowl many times, but never eaten at the restaurant before and I wanted to eat the food straight from the kitchen. First of we get there there is no one in the restaurant and it seemed like they were upset that we decided to eat in. The portion sizes are great but there was no way we were going to finish all of it so we asked for containers. The waitress brought us the containers but kept taking the plates that we were trying take with us. As I was putting away my pad Thai, they took two of my plates that I was going to take home! Also important to note that I ordered a soup asked for a soup container and was given the rice container! When I asked for a different container at least a plastic container, which I know they have bc I have ordered from them before, the waitress said sorry we don't have any! What!!! Literally was in there for 10 minutes when the check was brought to my table! Talk about horrible customer service! The food is not the problem! Eat the food it is delicious! But be warned the decir in the tatami rant is HORRIBLE!
I really wish they improved

If you're near UIC in Chicago, you have to stop by Thai Bowl and try their Pad Thai. Its really great! It's a nice little restaurant located right on Taylor Street. And don't forget to show them your UIC school ID because they give a student discount.
Very good food, great customer service, and clean establishment
Best Thai food around. The outdoor seating is awesome, too. Try it!
Used to love this place, ate there today and there were egg shells in my freaking food. Gross

I don't usually rate places unless they are really good or really bad. Unfortunately, after coming back here for the third time, reluctantly, nothing changed for the better. The decor is like high school lunch room with uncomfortable plastic/wooden chairs and the lady behind the cashier is also like a lunch lady who hates her job. The first time I went they served the wrong soup and then still charged me for it and had an attitude about a refund. The food does not taste fresh like it has been taken from the left-overs of a china buffet and there is no lunch special so it is over-priced with no extra egg roll or soup. Maybe I am being a bit harsh but hopefully they can take note and maybe make some changes. Seems like other people like this place so maybe it is just bad luck?
Worst I've ever had. Food was very dry and bland. Took two bites and ordered a pizza.
Pad thai the best

I really like it here the food is reasonably priced and everything is made to order. Their crab rangoon is really good one of the best that I have ever tasted. They have really good food I also order the Jade noodle dish. I have never been disappointed eating here.
Best in the city that I have visited.

o start, my background with them is that I have been going here for over 10 years now. My company UPS has been getting delivery from here for almost as long because of my referral.  So now 9 months to the day pregnant and I order  a pick-up order to get my spicy food to help with delivery and I have to deal with this supposed "manager" named, Eial.  I was disconnected twice and when she received my order I chose my free appetizer like I always do  and she had the audacity to deny me because my bill was 15 cents under!  Not dollars cents! I have never had anyone make such a petty discrepancy after all the time I have been going here!  It shocked me further that she was the manager too?!  I am very disappointed and find after me explaining my loyalty to them still having no factor really disheartening. Think I am going to have to find a new Thai place....
Worst pad see ew I've ever had.  Girlfriend got thin noodles I think.  That tasted probably even worse.  Was quite disappointing as we had heard from a friend that this place was good.

This is a college past time favorite. I get nostalgic every time I order from here. Good cheap eats. I always order the Thai Iced tea, beef pad see ew, chicken pad thai and shrimp fried rice. The portions are plentiful. I would get carry out here over any thai place in Chicago.
Good Thai food on Taylor.  There are better places, IMHO, but this place is reliable for a good meal.

I have been a patron for 10 years. Best thai food in the area. I really like their pad thai, green curry (very spicy but delish), and asian beef and noodle. Their service could be better, but not the worst. They have a really nice outdoor eating space with trees and lights at night.
The place is clean and services is good.  I really enjoy the Thai Bowl mix Rice dish.  It has shirp, chicken, vegetables with beef.  I enjoyed the outside patio in a Summer day.
Great Thai food with nice staffs. I like the restaurant decoration too. The price is acceptable compared to others Thai restaurant in the neiborghood. A nice reaturant to try Thai dishes.

In my opinion, the best thai food in chicago. Their chicken pad thai is to die for. Prices can be rather high, though all thai food tends to be spicy. This will definitely fill you up though, the portions are generous. Amazing place.

I come here so much despite their bad service and that should tell you how good the food is. Every single time I come here they make me wait over 40 mins for my noodles on top of the 30 min wait to get my order taken but that's okay because I'm willing to wait for their Jade Noodles :) Most things on the menu cost around $9-11 but my only advice would be not to come starving because they even take long with their starters. They also have some of the best hot tea around.
If you are a student at UIC, they have an a nice discount. The food is slightly better than average but much better than subways! this is something I would recommend

Not nearly as spicy as I like my Thai food, but it was still decent. It's in a cool neighborhood but other than that the decor is nothing special. The smoothies are pretty good. As far as west side places go it's the best Thai you're gonna get.
I love the Jade noodles! They dont have the best of service but they have a nice outdoor patio that is perfect in the summer.
It is cheap here with good food.
Stop here for a quick Thai fix!

A great find if you're looking for a casual, inexpensive, tasty and filling dinner. You can do takeout, eat in or in their outside seating area when it's nice outside. The wait staff was less than impressive, but taken price into account overall, not bad!

Great Thai food at its finest and great portions. It also serves a variety of Asian food. In the summer it has outside seating for some great time in the open. If you've never tried Thai food, go for  the chicken pad Thai!
The food was tasty. However the waitress did not check up on her customers often and I  would have appreciated better and faster service. I would still recommend this restaurant!
Thai Bowl was my lunch spot throughout college. Whenever someone asks me for a great thai place this is the place to go! Their Pad Thai is spectacular!
it's near to my school UIC  and the food is good with the price is decent
cheap but too sweet for me
Great thai food, student discount w id..fresh spring rolls yum.
They forgot our order, and when we reminded them, the food they brought to us was terrible
One of my favorite thai places in the area. I recommend the chicken pad thai!
